  "description": "Two redundant cooling trains (pump → heat exchanger) with a cross-tie valve that lets train A's pump feed train B's exchanger. That cross-tie makes the network NON series-parallel — it cannot be reduced by the usual series/parallel folding, and is solved from its minimal path sets by inclusion-exclusion: {PMP-A,HX-A}, {PMP-B,HX-B}, {PMP-A,XTIE,HX-B}. It is the classic bridge structure, and the reason this tool solves general two-terminal networks rather than only nested series/parallel ones. Rates are per hour: pumps λ=3e-5 (MTBF ≈ 33,000 h, MTTR 8 h), heat exchangers λ=5e-6 (fouling; MTTR 50 h), cross-tie valve λ=1e-5 (MTTR 16 h). Try reliability at the 8760 h mission, then availability, then delete the cross-tie and re-run to see exactly what the extra path buys you.",
